===Verb===
'''to ping''' ([[pings]], [[pinged]], [[pinging]])

#To emit a signal and then listen for its echo in order to detect objects.
# (''networking'') To send an packet in order to determine whether a [[host]] is present.
#: ''I'm pinging kremvax.''
# (''networking'') To send a packet and receive a response indicating that the host is present.
#: ''I can't ping kremvax.''
#To send an email or other message to someone in hopes of eliciting a response.
#: ''I'll ping the insurance company again to see if they've received our claim.''

===Noun===
'''ping''' ([[pings]])


# A signal, packet or other message produced for the purpose of pinging.
#: ''The submarine sent out a ping and found a battleship.''
#: ''The network is overloaded from all the pings.''
#: ''I sent a ping to the insurance company but they haven't got back to me.''

===Proper noun===

# (''computing'') The ping network utility.  (''Note: not generally capitalized'').
# (''golf'') A manufacturer of golf clubs.

